            "source": [
                "# Real World Use Case: Medical Imaging (MRI vs Pathology)\n",
                "\n",
                "**Scenario**: You are building an AI for a hospital.\n",
                "*   **MRI/X-Ray**: These are machines that measure density. They are **Grayscale** (1 Channel).\n",
                "*   **Pathology/Skin Lesion**: These are photos of tissue. They are **RGB** (3 Channels).\n",
                "\n",
                "**Goal**: Handle different input shapes dynamically (1 vs 3 channels) so your model doesn't crash."
            ]
        },
        {
            "cell_type": "code",
            "execution_count": null,
            "metadata": {},
            "outputs": [],
            "source": [
                "import numpy as np\n",
                "\n",
                "def check_medical_image(image):\n",
                "    # Image shape expectation: (H, W, C)\n",
                "    if len(image.shape) == 2:\n",
                "        print(f\"Detected X-Ray/MRI (Grayscale). Shape: {image.shape}. Adding channel dim...\")\n",
                "        # Add the missing channel dimension\n",
                "        image = np.expand_dims(image, axis=-1)\n",
                "        print(f"Fixed Shape: {image.shape
                }\")\n",
                "        return image\n",
                "    elif len(image.shape) == 3 and image.shape[2] == 3:\n",
                "        print(f\"Detected Skin/Pathology (RGB). Shape: {image.shape}. Good to go.\")\n",
                "        return image\n",
                "    else:\n",
                "        print(f\"Error: Unknown format {image.shape}\")\n",
                "        return None\n",
                "\n",
                "# 1. Mock MRI (256x256)\n",
                "mri = np.zeros((256, 256))\n",
                "processed_mri = check_medical_image(mri)\n",
                "\n",
                "# 2. Mock Skin Photo (256x256x3)\n",
                "skin = np.zeros((256, 256, 3))\n",
                "processed_skin = check_medical_image(skin)\n",
                "\n",
                "# 3. Mock 4D Video (Error)\n",
                "video = np.zeros((10, 256, 256, 3))\n",
                "check_medical_image(video)"
            ]
        },
        {
            "cell_type": "markdown",
            "metadata": {},
            "source": [
                "## Conclusion\n",
                "In the real world, you cannot assume shape. You must check and fix (Standardize) your inputs before feeding them to a CNN."
            ]
        }
    ],
